# ==============================================================================
#  .gitignore — MoDirect-Analysis
#
#  RULE: EVERY PATTERN IS ANCHORED WITH A LEADING "/".
#
#  An unanchored pattern in git matches at EVERY level of the tree, not just the
#  root. That is not a style preference here; it destroyed work in the previous
#  repo (cross-modal-info). Its .gitignore contained bare rules:
#
#      scripts/          <- intended: a throwaway root-level scratch dir
#      *.json            <- intended: bulky cached blobs
#      analysis/swap_intervention/
#
#  "scripts/" matched analysis/factorial_experiment/scripts/ — the entire factorial
#  intervention codebase. "*.json" matched its results/*.json alongside it. Neither
#  was ever staged, so `git status` stayed clean and nothing ever warned. That code
#  has NO commit and NO history: it is PERMANENTLY LOST AND UNRECOVERABLE.
#
#  So: anchor every rule, and scope ignores to the exact directory you mean.
#  Never write a bare directory name. Never blanket-ignore a source extension.
#  Before adding a rule, run:  git status --ignored  and read what it swallowed.
# ==============================================================================

# ------------------------------------------------------------------ python
/**/__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
/*.egg-info/
/build/
/dist/
/.venv/
/venv/

# ------------------------------------------------------------------ editor / tooling
/.vscode/
/.idea/
/.pytest_cache/
/.claude/

# ------------------------------------------------------------------ heavy generated tensors
# Per-identity averaged hidden states, regenerable by
# pipeline/04_concepts/11_extract_per_identity.py (44M in the old repo).
# Anchored to the exact directory — NOT a bare "per_identity_avg/".
/pipeline/04_concepts/per_identity_avg/
/experiments/**/per_identity_avg/

# ------------------------------------------------------------------ logs
# 103 files / 30M in the old repo. Extensions are safe to match broadly (no source
# file uses them); directories are not, so log DIRS are anchored explicitly.
*.log
*.out
*.err
/logs/
/pipeline/**/logs/
/experiments/**/logs/

# ------------------------------------------------------------------ run outputs
# Result trees are regenerable and large. Anchored so that a future
# "results.py" module or docs/results.md is never caught.
/results/
/output/
/output_*/
/outputs/
/previous_output/
/linear_probe_features/

# ------------------------------------------------------------------ host-specific runners
# z_script/ holds THIS host's launch scripts (conda paths, node-local caches,
# SLURM partition, sbatch wrappers). Deliberately untracked: recreate per host
# from z_script/README.md; the portable logic lives in pipeline/ and modirect/.
/z_script/

# ==============================================================================
#  DELIBERATELY COMMITTED — do not add ignore rules that would catch these.
#  Listed as explicit un-ignores so the intent survives future edits.
# ==============================================================================

# Concept vectors: 8 files x 404K = 3.2M. Small, stable, and the reproducible
# input to every intervention — checked in on purpose.
!/assets/concept_vectors/*.pt

# Vision-side direction axes (436K total).
!/assets/vision_axes/*.npz

# Paper figures (png/pdf).
!/docs/figures/**

# The task registry that core/dataset_loader.py:119 discovers at import time.
# If these are ever ignored, discover_tasks() returns an EMPTY registry silently.
!/tasks/**/*.yaml
!/tasks/**/utils.py

# Run configs.
!/configs/*.yaml

# …except the host-local override, documented as untracked in
# modirect/config/paths.py ("checked-in-by-the-user overrides (gitignored)").
# Must come AFTER the un-ignore above to win.
/configs/paths.yaml
